WEBVTT

00:05.046 --> 00:07.757
(theme music playing)

00:18.268 --> 00:21.604
♪ Got a secret,
can you keep it ♪

00:21.688 --> 00:24.858
♪ Swear this one
you'll save ♪

00:24.941 --> 00:28.319
♪ Better lock it
in your pocket ♪

00:28.403 --> 00:30.905
♪ Taking this one
to the grave ♪

00:30.989 --> 00:35.535
♪ If I show you
then I know you ♪

00:35.618 --> 00:38.705
♪ Won't tell what I said ♪

00:38.788 --> 00:42.250
♪ 'Cause two can
keep a secret ♪

00:42.333 --> 00:45.211
♪ If one of them is dead ♪

00:49.424 --> 00:52.635
♪ 'Cause two can
keep a secret ♪

00:52.719 --> 00:55.013
♪ 'Cause two can
keep a secret ♪

00:55.096 --> 00:58.808
♪ 'Cause two
can keep a secret ♪

00:58.892 --> 01:03.229
♪ If one of them is dead ♪

01:08.526 --> 01:11.154
(rock music playing)

01:13.198 --> 01:14.783
(laughing)

01:16.701 --> 01:18.036
♪ It's partytime ♪

01:25.376 --> 01:27.128
(sniffs)
Ugh, it smells.

01:27.212 --> 01:29.005
(all laughing)

01:29.088 --> 01:30.965
-What's in it?
-Dog shit, of course.

01:31.049 --> 01:33.802
You're gonna throw it
against that door.

01:36.387 --> 01:39.057
It's part of our...
initiation.

01:41.601 --> 01:44.354
-What if they see me?
-Oh, don't you worry.

01:44.437 --> 01:45.772
We got you.

01:53.154 --> 01:55.281
-I don't wanna do it, guys.
-Sidney: Come on.

01:55.365 --> 01:59.536
And then we'll go
to Pinball Pizza
for garlic knots.

01:59.619 --> 02:00.787
Come on.

02:00.870 --> 02:03.039
-(group laughing)
-Davie: Angela...

02:04.916 --> 02:07.585
(ominous music playing)

02:15.593 --> 02:17.345
(car starts)

02:17.428 --> 02:18.721
(laughing)

02:23.059 --> 02:24.227
Homeowner:
Michael, call the police!

02:30.441 --> 02:33.194
I knew it.
This all goes back
to our mothers,

02:33.278 --> 02:34.195
and Angela.

02:34.279 --> 02:37.574
-What did your mom do to her?
-I don't know.

02:37.657 --> 02:39.367
A said my mom threw
Angela under the bus.

02:39.450 --> 02:44.247
-What did A do to you?
-He went full fucking
Michael Myers.

02:44.330 --> 02:46.875
He chased me around
my building onto the roof.

02:46.958 --> 02:48.585
Okay, this is getting
beyond dangerous now.

02:48.668 --> 02:50.962
What do we do?

02:51.045 --> 02:53.798
Is it time to...
tell someone?

02:53.882 --> 02:55.341
We can't.

02:55.425 --> 02:58.428
We're so close
to understanding why
this is all happening,

02:58.511 --> 03:01.431
why... us.

03:01.514 --> 03:03.474
Plus, after what
Noa went through,

03:03.558 --> 03:04.934
not sure we should
be disobeying A

03:05.018 --> 03:07.103
and telling
anyone anything.

03:07.186 --> 03:10.148
Angela isn't mentioned
anywhere in my mom's diaries.

03:10.231 --> 03:14.652
But now, we know for sure
there's a connection.

03:14.736 --> 03:17.030
So, the missing pages
could be about Angela.

03:17.113 --> 03:19.073
I've been going through
all the stuff at my house,

03:19.157 --> 03:21.743
but now that I know
what I'm looking for...

03:21.826 --> 03:23.578
I feel like I have
to start over.

03:23.661 --> 03:24.913
We can help.

03:24.996 --> 03:26.664
Should we meet after school?

03:26.748 --> 03:28.875
I'll bring walkie-talkies
from my mom's pawn shop.

03:30.001 --> 03:32.754
Trust me... they're rad.

03:32.837 --> 03:35.465
-(bell rings)
-Hey, Tabby, wait up! Tabby!

03:35.548 --> 03:37.425
Is everything okay?
You didn't say two words
to me in Smithee's class.

03:37.508 --> 03:39.844
Was there, was there
something wrong with
the footage that I shot?

03:39.928 --> 03:41.971
It's not what
you shot, Chip.

03:42.055 --> 03:44.682
It's that you shot it.

03:44.766 --> 03:46.935
(sighs)
This whole exercise
was supposed to be

03:47.018 --> 03:49.103
about changing the tired
dynamics of horror

03:49.187 --> 03:51.773
in front of
and behind the camera.

03:51.856 --> 03:53.441
Male victim,
female killer.

03:53.524 --> 03:55.068
Female director
with a female gaze.

03:55.151 --> 03:57.946
You stepping in to take over
completely invalidated that.

03:58.029 --> 04:00.782
Shit, Tabby, I'm...
(inhales)

04:00.865 --> 04:05.286
I'm really, really
sorry about all of it.

04:05.370 --> 04:06.329
Honestly, I was just
trying to help.

04:09.082 --> 04:11.542
Forget it.
I gotta go meet the girls.

04:15.964 --> 04:18.299
♪ ♪

04:19.217 --> 04:21.511
Faran: (on walkie-talkie)
Hello?

04:22.679 --> 04:24.138
Faran?
Did you find something?

04:24.222 --> 04:27.600
(chuckles) Not yet,
but I made popcorn.

04:27.684 --> 04:29.352
Is that what I'm smelling?

04:29.435 --> 04:31.062
It might've singed a little.

04:31.145 --> 04:33.189
There's nothing
in the garage.

04:33.272 --> 04:35.316
But I'll try the back
of the house.

04:35.400 --> 04:38.486
-Tabby? Anything?
-I'm heading downstairs
right now.

04:38.569 --> 04:39.654
-Noa: (on walkie) Guys, guys!
-Noa, are you okay?

04:39.737 --> 04:42.323
(grunts) I'm fine,

04:42.407 --> 04:45.827
except your attic
is a fucking spider Airbnb.

04:47.078 --> 04:48.788
Tabby, how's the basement?

04:50.164 --> 04:51.958
Super dark.

04:52.041 --> 04:55.628
-(flicks light switch)
-(sighs) The light's out.

04:55.712 --> 04:57.255
Imogen: (on walkie)
There's another switch
at the bottom of the steps.

04:59.132 --> 04:59.173
(sighs)

05:08.141 --> 05:10.101
(tense music playing)

05:10.184 --> 05:10.268
I'm a final girl.

05:12.645 --> 05:14.022
I'm a final girl.

05:14.981 --> 05:16.774
I'm a final girl.

05:16.858 --> 05:19.027
Not gonna lie,
this is creepy AF.

05:19.110 --> 05:21.904
Faran: (on walkie)
Ch-ch-ch-ah-ah-ah.

05:21.988 --> 05:24.824
Actually,
it's kee-kee-kee-ma-ma-ma,

05:24.907 --> 05:28.202
as in when Mrs. Voorhees says
"killer mommy" in Jason's voice.

05:28.286 --> 05:30.705
Great.
Thanks for movie-splaining
that to me.

05:30.788 --> 05:32.415
(door creaking)

05:41.466 --> 05:43.217
Mr. Hammond, I think
we're back in business.

05:48.139 --> 05:51.100
Faran: (on walkie)
Guys, living room now!

05:56.147 --> 05:59.233
I found these
in the fireplace.

05:59.317 --> 05:59.400
Shit.

06:02.195 --> 06:03.529
Are those the pages?

06:08.659 --> 06:09.702
Hey.

06:10.995 --> 06:13.831
They could be
from anything...

06:13.915 --> 06:15.875
like a pad of paper
or a notebook--

06:15.958 --> 06:18.628
Or they are my mom's
diary pages.

06:18.711 --> 06:21.756
Which, let's face it,
we were never gonna find.

06:24.217 --> 06:25.426
Imogen.

06:27.845 --> 06:30.431
It's like everything
in my life is slipping
away from me,

06:30.515 --> 06:31.682
and...

06:31.766 --> 06:35.061
there's nothing
I can do to stop it.

06:35.144 --> 06:36.729
First, my body,
then my mom,
now our house,

06:36.813 --> 06:40.274
and I can't-- I...

06:40.358 --> 06:42.360
I can't leave it,
not with all
these questions.

06:46.864 --> 06:49.117
You guys,
I don't wanna sell
my mom's house.

06:49.784 --> 06:50.743
What if...

06:50.827 --> 06:53.287
you take it over?

06:53.371 --> 06:56.249
The mortgage...
payments or whatever.

06:56.332 --> 06:57.333
We could talk to my mom,

06:57.416 --> 06:59.001
find out exactly how much
money you'd need--

06:59.085 --> 07:02.338
I have $400 in the bank...

07:02.421 --> 07:05.925
that I saved from, like,
my last 10 birthdays.

07:07.927 --> 07:09.595
Where would I get the money?

07:15.935 --> 07:20.148
So, Henry, how'd it go?
Does Kelly have a scar?

07:21.858 --> 07:23.317
I offered her a foot rub.

07:25.403 --> 07:26.237
And?

07:28.656 --> 07:30.616
-Am I crazy?
-No.

07:30.700 --> 07:32.493
You were right.
She does have a scar.

07:32.577 --> 07:36.122
-On her foot.
-Oh... my god.

07:36.205 --> 07:39.667
But Faran, there are
a number of reasons why
she could have scars.

07:39.750 --> 07:44.380
-This doesn't necessarily
mean that Kelly's--
-Karen?

07:44.463 --> 07:47.008
Maybe. Maybe not.

07:47.091 --> 07:51.012
But something very weird
is going on here.

07:54.140 --> 07:55.850
Steve: (on computer)
Hey there.
Where did you vanish to?

07:55.933 --> 07:57.059
I was worried.

07:57.143 --> 07:57.894
Nowhere.

07:57.977 --> 08:00.271
I didn't have access
to my devices.

08:00.354 --> 08:03.524
Sorry, I didn't
mean to ghost you.

08:03.608 --> 08:04.442
How've you been?

08:05.193 --> 08:06.152
Okay.

08:07.320 --> 08:09.363
Wondering if you've given
any more thought to

08:09.447 --> 08:11.073
what we were discussing.

08:12.283 --> 08:13.993
About meeting in person?

08:14.076 --> 08:15.369
We've been chatting
for weeks now,

08:15.453 --> 08:18.664
and... don't forget,
you reached out to me.

08:18.748 --> 08:21.292
I did.
And I found a place...

08:21.375 --> 08:22.460
where we could meet.

08:23.502 --> 08:25.046
It's private...

08:25.129 --> 08:27.006
where we could have a...

08:27.757 --> 08:28.674
nice dinner...

08:30.134 --> 08:32.136
and wouldn't bump into anybody.

08:32.220 --> 08:33.471
That sounds perfect.

08:33.554 --> 08:36.015
But, Steve, a--
after dinner,

08:36.098 --> 08:37.975
could we go
trick-or-treating?

08:38.809 --> 08:40.686
I've never gone.

08:40.770 --> 08:41.896
My moms never let me.

08:41.979 --> 08:43.731
Rachel loved
trick-or-treating.

08:43.814 --> 08:47.235
It was one of her
favorite things.
Let's do it.

08:47.318 --> 08:48.361
Mouse:
Okay, great.

08:48.444 --> 08:51.072
But, uh, I-I-I'll
have to buy a costume.

08:51.155 --> 08:53.241
Did Rachel have any...

08:54.158 --> 08:55.284
favorites?

08:55.368 --> 08:57.870
Steve:
Just nothing too scary.

08:57.954 --> 09:00.289
Will you send me
some options?

09:00.373 --> 09:01.499
I'll treat, of course.

09:03.167 --> 09:04.335
Sure.

09:05.628 --> 09:06.420
I'm excited.

09:16.013 --> 09:18.432
(sentimental music playing)

09:23.646 --> 09:25.940
-Imogen: Did you make this?
-Davie: For the baby.

09:26.023 --> 09:28.109
-Thank you.
-Hm.

09:28.651 --> 09:30.861
It's beautiful.

09:34.073 --> 09:36.117
I was thinking
we should have
a baby shower.

09:36.200 --> 09:39.161
Oh, Mom,
I love my quilt,

09:39.245 --> 09:41.163
but can we please
skip the party?

09:42.331 --> 09:43.708
If that's how
you want it to be.

09:45.876 --> 09:48.129
-Hm.
-But just know
you're missing out

09:48.212 --> 09:50.131
-on lots of presents.
-(chuckles)

09:50.715 --> 09:52.675
And cold, hard cash.

09:55.886 --> 09:57.930
♪ ♪

10:00.891 --> 10:05.313
Faran, even from you,
that is a wild accusation.

10:05.396 --> 10:08.441
It sounds that way...
but I have proof.

10:08.524 --> 10:12.028
Kelly has scars on her feet.

10:12.111 --> 10:13.821
Scars like Karen would have

10:13.904 --> 10:14.989
from when she stepped
on those razorblades.

10:15.072 --> 10:18.409
Stop... talking.

10:26.125 --> 10:28.836
I don't normally
share details about
students' personal lives,

10:28.919 --> 10:31.172
but Faran...

10:32.965 --> 10:34.842
you need to stop
this line of inquiry.

10:34.925 --> 10:40.389
In the past,
Kelly has engaged
in acts of self-harm.

10:40.473 --> 10:42.099
Self-harm, like...

10:44.101 --> 10:45.186
cutting?

10:45.936 --> 10:47.188
On the soles of her feet?

10:47.271 --> 10:51.817
People who self-harm
often do it in places
others won't see.

10:53.235 --> 10:55.529
I cannot and will not
say any more

10:55.613 --> 10:59.533
but I strongly
advise you drop this.

11:04.955 --> 11:08.751
Crazy Hail Mary idea
to save my house.

11:08.834 --> 11:11.128
What if we throw
an epic Halloween party

11:11.212 --> 11:14.131
and charge admission
as like a fundraiser?

11:14.215 --> 11:17.968
Girl, do we even know
enough people to invite
to a house party?

11:18.052 --> 11:20.846
Noa, Shawn's popular.
Can he get people to come?

11:20.930 --> 11:23.849
(laughs) Sure,
he can spread the word
to the football team.

11:24.725 --> 11:27.228
Uh, I have plans.

11:27.311 --> 11:28.646
Uh, I-I gotta help
my moms do inventory

11:28.729 --> 11:32.483
-at the pawn shop.
-On Halloween night?

11:32.566 --> 11:34.777
-Maybe I can come by after.
-Mm-hm.

11:34.860 --> 11:37.279
Although,
Ash did ask if I have
plans for Halloween.

11:37.363 --> 11:41.200
-(all gasping)
-He's cute.

11:41.283 --> 11:44.453
Mouse, you should
help your moms...

11:44.537 --> 11:45.871
and then come to the party.

11:45.955 --> 11:47.456
And tell Ash
to meet you there
and to bring friends.

11:47.540 --> 11:50.793
We need as many warm
bodies as possible.

11:50.876 --> 11:52.962
We can charge for slices
and shots, too.

11:53.045 --> 11:56.590
Yeah, it just needs
to be enough to start
making payments, right?

11:56.674 --> 11:58.300
Correct.

11:58.384 --> 12:00.719
And worst-case
scenario...

12:00.803 --> 12:03.848
I'll get to have
one last amazing
night in my house.

12:03.931 --> 12:05.891
Totally.
Of course.

12:05.975 --> 12:07.017
I just...

12:07.101 --> 12:08.853
gotta swing by
the Orpheum first.

12:08.936 --> 12:11.897
-Mm.
-Gonna need some funds
to chip in for supplies.

12:15.943 --> 12:17.528
-(Mouse laughs)
-Ash: A party?

12:17.611 --> 12:18.446
Yeah. (laughs)

12:18.529 --> 12:20.656
Thought your moms
wouldn't let you out.

12:21.740 --> 12:24.618
I have to ask them, but...

12:24.702 --> 12:29.248
I think it's time I assert
a little independence.

12:29.331 --> 12:32.209
-I deserve to have, uh--
-A date?

12:34.712 --> 12:34.795
Yeah.

12:36.547 --> 12:37.298
A date.

12:37.381 --> 12:39.717
Should I pick you up?

12:40.092 --> 12:42.636
Um...

12:42.720 --> 12:44.847
Why don't I...
meet you there...

12:46.015 --> 12:47.308
at, like, 9:30?

12:50.311 --> 12:52.313
Tabby:
Wes, I need my last paycheck.

12:59.820 --> 13:03.115
Way to ghost me
the other night.
(sighs)

13:03.991 --> 13:07.453
Is that what
you think happened?

13:07.536 --> 13:10.164
Which is, to me,
Argento's masterpiece.

13:12.124 --> 13:16.420
One second,
I'm making dinner.
The next, you're gone.

13:16.504 --> 13:19.548
Wes, you used
the flash drive as leverage

13:19.632 --> 13:21.008
to lure me to your place.

13:21.091 --> 13:23.511
What you did was
really fucked up.
Triggering.

13:23.594 --> 13:24.637
Not to mention the fact
that we never unpacked

13:24.720 --> 13:28.015
that night
in your car when...

13:28.098 --> 13:28.766
you almost kissed me.

13:31.435 --> 13:34.730
Fuck... You're right.

13:34.813 --> 13:36.941
-Damn straight.
-And I'm sorry.

13:38.400 --> 13:41.153
I won't put you
in that position ever again.

13:41.946 --> 13:42.738
I mean it.

13:44.198 --> 13:45.407
'Cause I do care
about you, Tabby.

13:45.491 --> 13:48.410
Genuinely.
Not in a creepy way.

13:50.204 --> 13:53.207
Also,
there's still a job here
for you if you want it.

13:55.251 --> 13:57.378
I... don't know, Wes.

13:57.461 --> 14:00.422
I'll give you
first dibs on shifts.

14:00.506 --> 14:03.425
Take you off
bathroom duty... forever.

14:05.261 --> 14:06.929
Bathroom duty
is loathsome.

14:10.683 --> 14:10.724
Okay then.

14:12.518 --> 14:15.396
Excellent. (laughs)

14:15.479 --> 14:17.147
Look, uh, I don't wanna
put you on the spot,

14:17.231 --> 14:19.525
but Jackie bailed
on me for tomorrow,

14:19.608 --> 14:21.944
which is our all-day
Halloween horror-a-thon,

14:22.027 --> 14:24.488
-free concessions
for whoever comes in costume.
-Mm.

14:24.572 --> 14:26.740
Could you come in to help?

14:28.117 --> 14:29.243
During the day, yes,

14:29.326 --> 14:30.786
but... I have
a thing at night.

14:39.837 --> 14:41.130
Um...

14:41.213 --> 14:41.880
I'm going out
on Halloween night...

14:43.507 --> 14:45.634
to a party... with Ash.

14:46.385 --> 14:48.679
Who's Ash again?

14:49.179 --> 14:51.974
A... friend...

14:52.057 --> 14:54.226
-from school.
-What time's this party?

14:55.185 --> 14:56.937
It starts at, like, 7:30.

14:57.021 --> 14:59.189
You can absolutely go
to the party, Mouse,

14:59.273 --> 15:01.150
-but be home by--
-9:30.

15:02.109 --> 15:02.943
10:30.

15:04.403 --> 15:06.989
Please. Mom? I...

15:07.072 --> 15:09.575
I just want to be
a normal 15-year-old.

15:12.202 --> 15:13.579
10:30's fine.

15:16.540 --> 15:19.001
(rock music playing)

15:20.252 --> 15:23.464
♪ Spend my days
gassin' school ♪

15:23.547 --> 15:27.217
♪ Trashin' books
and breakin' rules ♪

15:27.301 --> 15:29.887
♪ Spend my nights
in a switchblade fight ♪

15:31.930 --> 15:34.224
(indistinct chatter)

15:34.308 --> 15:37.436
♪ She wants hot,
she wants cold ♪

15:37.519 --> 15:41.231
♪ I'm too hot to handle
and I'm too hot to hold ♪

15:41.315 --> 15:44.568
♪ She wants hot,
she wants cold ♪

15:44.652 --> 15:48.238
♪ ♪

15:55.287 --> 15:58.415
-How you doin'?
-That'll be eight bucks.

15:58.499 --> 16:01.835
-Thought this was free.
-For costumed patrons, yes.

16:01.919 --> 16:03.545
Wait...

16:03.629 --> 16:05.381
you made that sick
video about Karen.

16:05.464 --> 16:07.049
Only after you made yours.

16:07.132 --> 16:08.634
Well, you almost got
me in a lot of trouble.

16:08.717 --> 16:10.886
I did get in
a lot of trouble.

16:13.347 --> 16:15.182
Anything else I can get you?

16:15.265 --> 16:17.685
Yeah... Uh, Cherry Coke.

16:17.768 --> 16:20.437
We don't have cherry,
just regular.

16:20.521 --> 16:21.939
What about you?

16:22.022 --> 16:22.731
Still have your cherry?
(laughs)

16:22.815 --> 16:26.276
-Friend: Woo!
-(group laughing)

16:28.821 --> 16:29.947
Relax.
It's just a joke.

16:32.324 --> 16:33.742
-Don't be so uptight.
-Good one.

16:35.452 --> 16:38.455
♪ ♪

16:40.749 --> 16:43.168
("Moonchild" by
Marissa Nadler playing)

16:45.295 --> 16:49.883
♪ Call her moonchild ♪

16:49.967 --> 16:55.097
♪ Dancing in the shallows
of a river ♪

17:01.353 --> 17:09.028
♪ Waving silver wands
to the nightbirds' song ♪

17:09.111 --> 17:16.577
♪ Waiting for the sun
on the mountain ♪

17:16.660 --> 17:18.203
(camera clicks)

17:20.956 --> 17:25.002
♪ Ooh ♪

17:26.211 --> 17:28.922
Kelly:
I'm surprised you
wanted to meet up.

17:29.006 --> 17:30.340
I mean...

17:31.300 --> 17:33.010
God... (chuckles)

17:33.093 --> 17:34.052
-If Karen could see us now.
-Mm.

17:35.679 --> 17:35.971
If only.

17:38.640 --> 17:43.145
You know, I never
realized how great
of a dancer you are.

17:43.228 --> 17:45.814
You're really
coming into it.

17:45.898 --> 17:47.024
I've always been
a good dancer.

17:49.902 --> 17:52.362
I just wasn't
allowed to show it.

17:52.446 --> 17:53.822
What do you mean
"allowed"?

17:54.364 --> 17:55.365
Karen...

17:56.700 --> 17:58.368
always had to be the star.

17:59.495 --> 18:01.163
And if I started
to outshine her,

18:01.246 --> 18:01.914
she would put me
in my place.

18:01.997 --> 18:03.999
Sibling rivalry
is blood sport.

18:06.001 --> 18:08.879
I can't stop thinking
about her...

18:10.380 --> 18:12.299
especially the night
of the dance.

18:12.382 --> 18:16.345
(inhales)
I keep... playing
it out differently.

18:17.721 --> 18:19.973
You know,
me stopping Karen, or...

18:20.057 --> 18:22.976
me going up to the rafters
in her place, or...

18:24.853 --> 18:27.481
us both staying home.
Just--

18:28.398 --> 18:29.983
(exhales)

18:32.528 --> 18:33.195
What happened
to your hand?

18:41.912 --> 18:45.833
Did you...
do that to yourself?

18:47.751 --> 18:50.587
It's such a cliché, right?

18:52.506 --> 18:56.051
The ballerina
who gets stressed
and... hurts herself.

19:01.557 --> 19:03.016
-Please don't tell anyone.
-I won't.

19:06.395 --> 19:08.188
And Kelly...

19:09.565 --> 19:13.861
if you're ever feeling
overwhelmed, or lonely,

19:13.944 --> 19:18.657
or... you need
someone to talk to...

19:18.740 --> 19:20.242
you can talk to me.

19:21.410 --> 19:22.452
I mean it.

19:24.204 --> 19:25.747
Thanks, Faran.

19:27.499 --> 19:29.209
Also...

19:29.293 --> 19:30.752
Imogen's having a party
at her old house tonight.

19:30.836 --> 19:33.255
Kinda like a fundraiser...

19:34.214 --> 19:35.424
but it'll be a good time.

19:35.507 --> 19:38.218
You should come...
if you want.

19:41.805 --> 19:44.266
("Dead Man's Party"
by Oingo Boingo playing)

19:44.808 --> 19:46.143
(all cheering)

19:48.270 --> 19:51.231
♪ Walkin' with a dead man
over my shoulder ♪

19:52.983 --> 19:53.192
It's amazing in here.

19:54.818 --> 19:55.903
Noa:
Hi!

19:55.986 --> 19:58.947
-Aww! Oh!
-Hi!

19:59.031 --> 20:00.240
Wow.

20:00.324 --> 20:02.659
You guys make an amazing

20:02.743 --> 20:05.787
Gomez/Morticia power couple.
(laughs)

20:05.871 --> 20:08.415
Wait, no.
Your money's no good here.

20:08.498 --> 20:11.126
Noa told me about
saving your house.
We wanna help.

20:11.209 --> 20:13.420
(sighs)
Thank you, Shawn.

20:13.503 --> 20:14.212
It's very kind of you.

20:14.296 --> 20:16.506
Would you grab me
a drink, babe?

20:16.590 --> 20:19.384
-You got it. Is it, um--
-Oh, that way.

20:19.468 --> 20:22.971
♪ Goin' to a party where
no one's still alive ♪

20:23.680 --> 20:24.890
Damn, Bryant...

20:26.058 --> 20:29.603
you could poison me any time.

20:29.686 --> 20:32.689
Who are you supposed to be?
Toxic Masculinity Smurf?

20:33.273 --> 20:35.484
Try Studly Smurf.

20:36.818 --> 20:38.070
What're you doin' after this?

20:38.153 --> 20:40.614
Going home, I imagine.

20:40.697 --> 20:43.825
-With me?
-(chuckles) Tyler.

20:43.909 --> 20:47.579
I'm sure there are
plenty of sad,

20:47.663 --> 20:50.624
desperate girls around here
who would be into...

20:50.707 --> 20:52.250
whatever this is,

20:52.334 --> 20:54.294
but I'm not one of them.

20:54.378 --> 20:57.464
Besides,
I like someone else
in my ballet class.

20:57.547 --> 20:58.799
What, some gay dude?

21:00.384 --> 21:03.011
Charming as ever. Bye.

21:04.763 --> 21:07.641
-Who invited you
to this party?
-My boy, Greg.

21:07.724 --> 21:09.309
Your leading man.

21:09.393 --> 21:13.146
-He's around here somewhere.
-Greg's here after he--

21:15.023 --> 21:17.985
You guys must go
to a lot of parties,
being so popular,

21:18.068 --> 21:20.821
-every weekend, I bet?
-I mean, yeah, sure.

21:20.904 --> 21:24.658
Well,
you were both at Karen's
house party, obviously.

21:24.741 --> 21:26.284
What about the one
over the summer

21:26.368 --> 21:27.828
in the woods
behind the school
with a bonfire?

21:27.911 --> 21:30.372
Were you there? Was Greg?

21:30.455 --> 21:33.083
-Fuck if I know.
-Oh, you don't remember?

21:33.166 --> 21:35.210
-You were that drunk?
-We party in the woods
all the time,

21:35.293 --> 21:37.004
but I don't remember
any bonfire.

21:37.087 --> 21:40.048
-Satisfied?
-No... Not even close.

21:41.133 --> 21:44.970
You're a garbage
person, Tyler.

21:45.053 --> 21:47.389
You and all your
fucking meathead
football buddies are.

21:47.472 --> 21:51.268
So, stay away from me,
and stay away from my friends.

21:51.351 --> 21:53.437
-Got it?
-Whatever.

21:56.523 --> 21:59.484
("Super Freak"
by Rick James playing)

21:59.568 --> 22:00.360
Both: (singing)
♪ She's a super freak ♪

22:00.444 --> 22:04.823
♪ Super freak,
she's super freaky ♪

22:04.906 --> 22:07.034
Steve:
I ordered your
favorite, Rachel.

22:07.117 --> 22:08.702
Breakfast for dinner.

22:10.787 --> 22:14.708
-(laughs)
-Even put the blueberries
in a smiley face...

22:14.791 --> 22:16.043
like you like.

22:20.130 --> 22:22.674
Did you bring
your report card?

22:22.758 --> 22:24.885
I know you
were struggling
with some classes.

22:24.968 --> 22:27.179
(fireworks popping)

22:27.262 --> 22:29.890
(cheering)

22:29.973 --> 22:32.059
(ominous music playing)

22:50.452 --> 22:54.414
("Little Monsters"
by The Foxies playing)

22:54.498 --> 22:58.502
♪ Little monsters,
tell me am I dead ♪

22:58.585 --> 23:02.714
♪ Little monsters,
all in my head ♪

23:02.798 --> 23:07.636
♪ A-All in my head ♪

23:10.305 --> 23:11.389
(ominous music playing)

23:39.626 --> 23:41.670
♪ ♪

23:55.225 --> 23:56.810
(kids laughing)

24:04.192 --> 24:05.318
You can call me
Dad if you want.

24:13.952 --> 24:15.996
♪ ♪

24:16.913 --> 24:18.456
(kids screaming)

24:23.378 --> 24:25.005
Mouse:
Trick or treat.

24:25.881 --> 24:26.840
(party music playing)

24:26.923 --> 24:29.968
(indistinct chatter)

24:37.601 --> 24:38.351
(sighs)

24:44.566 --> 24:46.193
Hey! What are you doing?

24:47.903 --> 24:49.738
Read the sign, asshole.

24:50.572 --> 24:52.699
There's another
one downstairs.

24:52.782 --> 24:54.534
This one's off limits.

24:54.618 --> 24:56.411
♪ ♪

25:02.876 --> 25:04.961
(exhales)

25:07.714 --> 25:10.091
So, are you
and Kelly BFFs now?

25:10.175 --> 25:11.843
Hardly.

25:11.927 --> 25:13.053
I don't know, Henry.

25:13.136 --> 25:15.472
Maybe I was going
full Natalie Portman

25:15.555 --> 25:16.056
"Black Swan" crazy.

25:16.139 --> 25:19.309
(laughs)
Yeah, could be.

25:19.392 --> 25:22.562
Or it could be that
you have a complicated
history with Karen

25:22.646 --> 25:24.564
that you're still
working through...

25:24.648 --> 25:26.441
and projecting onto Kelly.

25:27.192 --> 25:28.235
Yeah.

25:28.985 --> 25:29.986
Maybe.

25:32.322 --> 25:33.448
You know what?
(laughs)

25:35.116 --> 25:36.076
I'm letting it go.

25:36.159 --> 25:38.245
We're at a party.

25:39.162 --> 25:41.748
I should be having fun, right?

25:41.831 --> 25:43.750
Yeah, you should be.

25:43.833 --> 25:47.295
So, uh... let me
help you do that.

25:47.379 --> 25:48.630
("My Mistake" by Nina playing)

25:51.716 --> 25:55.220
♪ It wouldn't hurt
so bad at all ♪

26:00.517 --> 26:04.437
♪ If you anticipate
the fall ♪

26:08.858 --> 26:10.652
Steve:
No Reese's.
You're allergic to peanuts.

26:13.863 --> 26:17.325
And no candied apples.
There could be razorblades
or needles in them.

26:17.409 --> 26:20.078
-(laughing)
-(phone buzzing)

26:22.956 --> 26:26.042
It's 9:55.

26:27.252 --> 26:28.920
I should get to the party.

26:29.546 --> 26:30.630
I'm late.

26:32.215 --> 26:34.092
Can I drive you, please?

26:36.594 --> 26:37.554
I wouldn't forgive myself

26:37.637 --> 26:40.056
if anything bad
happened to you.

26:41.933 --> 26:44.811
Okay...

26:44.894 --> 26:48.148
but you have to drop me
off, like, a block away.

26:48.231 --> 26:50.025
If people saw us together,
it would be bad.

26:50.108 --> 26:52.319
I understand.

26:57.907 --> 26:58.908
Steve?

27:02.495 --> 27:03.538
I'm sorry.

27:04.581 --> 27:08.752
(cries)
I'm so, so sorry...
Rachel.

27:09.919 --> 27:11.212
It's okay.

27:12.464 --> 27:15.800
Please,
please forgive me.

27:15.884 --> 27:17.677
Hey, I-I-I do.

27:19.095 --> 27:20.722
I... forgive you.

27:22.098 --> 27:25.518
I forgive you... Dad.

27:26.186 --> 27:29.022
(dramatic music playing)

27:37.614 --> 27:41.493
("I Wanna" by
Potty Mouth playing)

27:41.576 --> 27:43.536
Kelly, look at that
theater kid. Nerd!

27:43.620 --> 27:47.123
♪ I wanna, I wanna,
I wanna, I wanna ♪

27:47.207 --> 27:49.709
♪ I wanna, I wanna,
I wanna... ♪

27:49.793 --> 27:51.378
(phone buzzing)

27:51.461 --> 27:53.046
♪ Wanna go where you go ♪

27:53.129 --> 27:54.172
♪ Wanna knowwhatchaknow ♪

27:54.255 --> 27:56.216
Hello?

27:56.299 --> 27:58.760
Yeah, this is Imogen Adams.
Who's this?

28:00.053 --> 28:03.014
Oh! Yes!
I did call about
Angela Waters.

28:03.098 --> 28:04.891
Let me get
somewhere quieter.

28:04.974 --> 28:07.268
Hello? Hello?

28:09.187 --> 28:10.480
Shit.

28:12.315 --> 28:13.483
(sighs)

28:13.566 --> 28:15.068
("The Spirit Knows"
by Goldminds playing)

28:15.151 --> 28:17.987
(indistinct chatter)

28:31.000 --> 28:32.669
Faran:
Kelly and Greg?

28:35.296 --> 28:37.382
I fucking knew it.

28:38.591 --> 28:40.176
(cheering)

28:43.596 --> 28:45.682
♪ Take me down ♪

28:46.266 --> 28:49.519
♪ To the world ♪

28:50.437 --> 28:52.814
♪ Underground ♪

28:53.606 --> 28:55.984
♪ I'm chasing ♪

28:57.318 --> 28:59.404
♪ Tiger snake ♪

29:01.322 --> 29:02.699
Mouse, you're here.

29:02.782 --> 29:06.411
Ash, wow, you went
with Freddie Mercury

29:06.494 --> 29:08.955
-and look incredible.
-Thanks.

29:09.038 --> 29:13.751
And you decided
to go... as--

29:13.835 --> 29:17.630
Oh, um...
I'm Wendy the Witch.

29:17.714 --> 29:20.675
Like from the comics
or the iconic
Hilary Duff movie.

29:20.758 --> 29:23.470
It came with a mask.
I could put it on.

29:23.553 --> 29:26.181
No way.
Then I wouldn't be
able to see your face.

29:26.264 --> 29:27.432
You look beautiful.

29:29.184 --> 29:30.143
I was starting to lose hope.

29:30.226 --> 29:31.936
I thought maybe
you stood me up.

29:32.020 --> 29:33.897
What? No, I...

29:33.980 --> 29:35.815
I really wanted to be
here with you, honest.

29:35.899 --> 29:38.234
I just...
had to deal with a, um--

29:38.318 --> 29:41.654
Let me guess,
childhood trauma?

29:43.114 --> 29:43.740
You know me so well.

29:45.283 --> 29:46.534
Not yet...

29:49.078 --> 29:50.371
but I want to.

29:51.956 --> 29:55.668
I think I'm ready
to close that sad
chapter in my book.

29:55.752 --> 30:01.216
-For good.
-What do you propose we do?

30:01.299 --> 30:03.885
You don't happen
to have any gummies,
do you?

30:09.224 --> 30:09.807
(muffled music playing)

30:13.436 --> 30:14.521
Chip:
Hey.

30:15.271 --> 30:17.065
Hey, Donnie Darko.

30:18.733 --> 30:20.026
When'd you get here?

30:20.109 --> 30:22.028
A while ago.

30:22.111 --> 30:25.949
-Pretty sure Imogen sold me,
like, five slices of pizza.
-(laughs)

30:28.034 --> 30:28.868
Peace offering?

30:28.952 --> 30:31.746
-Is it open?
-Ew, no, that'd be gross.

30:45.718 --> 30:48.972
-I talked to Smithee.
-Mm.

30:49.055 --> 30:51.724
I told him
what happened...

30:51.808 --> 30:54.227
and that we need
to do reshoots.

30:55.603 --> 30:59.857
-What'd he say?
-He gave us an extension...

30:59.941 --> 31:01.859
so you can shoot the scene.

31:05.363 --> 31:07.448
Thank you, Chip.

31:09.325 --> 31:11.828
But we might need
a new Norman Bates.
(chuckles)

31:13.371 --> 31:17.375
I'll be your Norman Bates.

31:17.458 --> 31:18.960
I mean,
I'll be wearing boxers
instead of a Speedo,

31:19.043 --> 31:23.673
but, yeah,
I'll embarrass the hell
out of myself for you.

31:23.756 --> 31:25.925
(Chip sighs)

31:26.009 --> 31:28.011
Do you, do you just
wanna get outta here?

31:28.094 --> 31:29.095
-(chuckles)
-We could watch

31:29.178 --> 31:32.098
"Nightmare on Elm Street."
It's your fave Freddy.

31:32.181 --> 31:35.560
-Mm, actually, "Dream Warriors"
was my fave Freddy.
-Mm.

31:35.643 --> 31:38.730
-(laughs) Yeah.
-That's right.

31:38.813 --> 31:41.149
I would, but...

31:41.232 --> 31:42.817
this night's
important to Imogen.

31:42.900 --> 31:43.985
I... I should stay.

31:45.278 --> 31:48.031
Yeah. Okay.

31:48.114 --> 31:49.699
Well, I'm gonna head out--

31:49.782 --> 31:51.451
-Hm.
-but...

31:51.534 --> 31:52.869
you call if you need me?

31:57.373 --> 31:59.250
-See ya later.
-(laughs)

32:02.045 --> 32:03.838
♪ ♪

32:04.422 --> 32:07.216
Having fun, Kelly?

32:09.093 --> 32:12.180
Oh, hey!
Yes, actually.

32:12.263 --> 32:14.807
-Thank you so much
for inviting me.
-Not a problem,

32:14.891 --> 32:18.311
but had I known you
were dating someone,

32:18.394 --> 32:20.104
I would've invited you both.

32:20.188 --> 32:23.107
What are you talking about?

32:23.191 --> 32:26.361
I saw you...
kissing Greg.

32:26.444 --> 32:28.571
-H-Hang on.
-Save it.

32:28.655 --> 32:30.323
This whole time you've been
gaslighting the school,

32:30.406 --> 32:31.658
you've been gaslighting me.

32:31.741 --> 32:32.909
God, I can't believe

32:32.992 --> 32:38.665
-I actually felt bad for you.
-No, girl, look,

32:38.748 --> 32:42.335
whatever you're thinking...
you're wrong.

32:42.418 --> 32:44.629
There's that word again.

32:46.381 --> 32:49.300
You know who used
to call me girl?

32:50.093 --> 32:50.927
Karen.

32:52.428 --> 32:57.183
-Okay?
-Henry says dancing with you
is like dancing with Karen.

32:57.266 --> 33:00.687
People don't suddenly become
amazing dancers overnight.

33:00.770 --> 33:02.355
And, now...

33:03.606 --> 33:07.193
you're kissing
Karen's boyfriend?

33:07.276 --> 33:10.655
Greg's... a friend.

33:10.738 --> 33:14.701
That was just
a... a moment.

33:14.784 --> 33:17.286
-We both miss her.
-Look, I'm just gonna say it.

33:18.121 --> 33:20.665
I don't think
you're Kelly.

33:23.376 --> 33:26.045
What? (scoffs)
Who else would I be?

33:26.129 --> 33:28.005
Karen...

33:28.089 --> 33:31.551
who sent Kelly up to the rafters
to do her dirty work,

33:31.634 --> 33:34.387
which makes total sense

33:34.470 --> 33:37.098
because that's what
Karen always did.

33:38.474 --> 33:42.729
(laughs)
Oh, you're spiraling.

33:42.812 --> 33:46.691
But then, Kelly died.

33:46.774 --> 33:50.820
And you don't want
people thinking you're
a horrible person,

33:50.903 --> 33:55.074
Karen, so instead,
you are pretending
to be Kelly,

33:55.158 --> 33:58.119
which makes a twisted
kind of sense.

33:58.202 --> 34:01.164
The only thing
that's twisted is you.

34:01.247 --> 34:03.958
And... why can't I be Kelly?

34:04.041 --> 34:07.545
Huh?
Why can't I be
a great dancer?

34:07.628 --> 34:09.047
Why can't I have
the hot boyfriend?

34:09.130 --> 34:10.173
Is it really
so hard to believe

34:10.256 --> 34:13.926
that Kelly Beasley
could be popular
and talented?

34:14.010 --> 34:17.889
You don't wanna
admit it... fine.

34:17.972 --> 34:23.311
But just know your life
may be in danger, Karen.

34:23.394 --> 34:29.984
-What did you say?
-Because, maybe,
Kelly didn't fall.

34:30.067 --> 34:35.948
Maybe someone pushed her,
thinking she was you, Karen.

34:36.032 --> 34:37.992
And now, that person
may be after you.

34:41.078 --> 34:43.206
Keep the hell away from me.

34:44.207 --> 34:45.625
I mean it, Faran.

34:45.708 --> 34:48.878
Don't you ever
talk to me again.

34:49.587 --> 34:51.297
You fucking psycho.

34:51.380 --> 34:53.257
(tense music playing)

34:55.885 --> 34:57.053
Ash:
How do you feel?

34:59.722 --> 35:00.014
Tingly.

35:03.226 --> 35:04.811
Fingers.

35:04.894 --> 35:07.480
("Better Than the Movies"
by Adore Delano playing)

35:07.563 --> 35:09.816
♪ Our names
written in the sky ♪

35:09.899 --> 35:12.318
♪ Everything is
ours tonight ♪

35:12.401 --> 35:13.486
My lips.

35:13.569 --> 35:16.823
♪ Gonna leave
it all to faith ♪

35:16.906 --> 35:20.201
♪ Show it off
like Phoebe Cates ♪

35:20.284 --> 35:23.788
♪ Live it up
and blame our age ♪

35:23.871 --> 35:27.291
♪ Young enough
to make mistakes ♪

35:29.085 --> 35:31.420
♪ Better than the movies ♪

35:31.504 --> 35:32.547
Wow.

35:32.630 --> 35:34.924
♪ Better than the movies ♪

35:36.342 --> 35:37.635
Also...

35:39.929 --> 35:41.097
I think I have
the munchies.

35:43.307 --> 35:45.101
(laughing)

35:48.563 --> 35:50.606
Same. (laughs)

35:53.109 --> 35:56.070
How about...
you stay here,

35:56.153 --> 36:00.241
and I'll go downstairs
and grab us some snacks?

36:00.324 --> 36:03.703
♪ Every time
we make a scene ♪

36:03.786 --> 36:07.081
♪ Life is like
a silver screen ♪

36:07.164 --> 36:09.709
♪ We were born
to take the lead ♪

36:09.792 --> 36:14.213
♪ Never gonna let it go ♪

36:14.297 --> 36:17.717
♪ Gonna give 'em all a show ♪

36:17.800 --> 36:19.635
♪ Walk into the afterglow ♪

36:19.719 --> 36:21.512
Hey, Teletubby.

36:22.847 --> 36:24.307
You here alone?

36:24.390 --> 36:26.225
You wanna see
my Tinky Winky?

36:26.309 --> 36:29.186
I'm not...
a Teletubby.

36:29.270 --> 36:30.563
And I'm with someone.

36:30.646 --> 36:32.565
Also, ew.

36:32.648 --> 36:33.900
Let me get you a drink.

36:33.983 --> 36:35.568
Stay here. I'll BRB.

36:36.277 --> 36:38.863
Oh my god,
you're here!

36:38.946 --> 36:40.531
(laughing)

36:41.657 --> 36:43.201
Bryant! Yes!
(laughs)

36:44.994 --> 36:48.456
Yo, Irish car bomb!
Take it!

36:48.539 --> 36:51.208
I-I'm good. Thanks.
My friends are here now.

36:51.292 --> 36:53.336
Yeah, all the more reason
to, like, loosen up.

36:53.419 --> 36:55.630
Tyler, she said she's good.

36:55.713 --> 36:58.215
Back off, Bryant.
Ya had your chance
with this.

36:58.299 --> 37:01.594
Settle down, Tyler,
or I'll get Shawn to beat
the shit out of you

37:01.677 --> 37:03.596
Yeah... or I'll just do it.

37:03.679 --> 37:05.556
Faran, come on.

37:05.640 --> 37:07.433
Give my boy Ty
here a chance.

37:07.516 --> 37:08.935
-He's good people.
-Oh, Greg,

37:09.018 --> 37:10.853
that couldn't be a more
meaningless endorsement

37:10.937 --> 37:11.938
coming from you.

37:12.021 --> 37:13.522
Yeah, I'm good, bro.
She ain't shit.

37:13.606 --> 37:15.107
But you, I mean,
you're pretty cute.

37:15.191 --> 37:15.942
Come on,
